                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14455538" author="krosenvold" created="Sat, 18 Aug 2012 14:41:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Added checks for various conditions that can cause &quot;groups&quot; to go ignored in r1374642. Also added explicit IT for excludedgroups&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14456684" author="tzvatot" created="Thu, 5 Feb 2015 08:01:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;@krosenvold&lt;br/&gt;
Can you please describe the fix? not sure what&apos;s the correct configuration should be.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14456675" author="tibor17" created="Fri, 6 Feb 2015 03:48:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I have tested excludedGroups with 2.18.1 which works for me as expected.&lt;br/&gt;
This means my test class is annotated with &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;@Category({SlowTest.class, SingleThreadTest.class})&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt; and &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;excludedGroups&amp;gt;pkg.SlowTest,pkg.SingleThreadTest&amp;lt;/excludedGroups&amp;gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;, and the test was not executed, and other categories were executed e.g. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;@Category(FastTest.class)&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14456667" author="tzvatot" created="Sun, 8 Feb 2015 02:33:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m using TestNG which configuration is a bit different. The excluded groups are strings, and the test classes are annotated with &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;@Test(groups = {&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;slow&quot;&lt;/span&gt;})&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14456502" author="tibor17" created="Sun, 8 Feb 2015 03:17:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;@Elad&lt;br/&gt;
TestNG 6.x is more buggy than 5.7.x.&lt;br/&gt;
Can you identify version of TestNG, and version of surefire where it is working and where it&apos;s not.&lt;br/&gt;
We would need project to reproduce the bug if it is our bug.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14456704" author="tzvatot" created="Sun, 8 Feb 2015 03:26:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;@Tibor&lt;br/&gt;
I&apos;m using TestNG version 6.8.5, surefire 2.13.&lt;br/&gt;
It seems the resolution of what are the tests to run is somewhat strange. I&apos;m trying to pin point the exact issue, but I suspect it&apos;s related to hierarchy of tests.&lt;br/&gt;
For example, for a base class SlowTest annotated with &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;@Test(groups = {&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;slow&quot;&lt;/span&gt;})&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;, I would expect that all sub classes that inherits from SlowTest will be skipped by surefire, and caught be failsafe. However, this is not the case, and I&apos;m trying to figure out the exact combination of @Test on the super/sub/method with/without group that will work.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14456683" author="tibor17" created="Mon, 9 Feb 2015 02:22:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It&apos;s hard to discuss like this. First of all you should run a simplistic test in IDE and surefire based on 5.7 and then compare.&lt;br/&gt;
Later switch to TestNG 6.8.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14456696" author="tzvatot" created="Mon, 9 Feb 2015 02:40:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Looks like 5.7 is no longer on maven central.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://central.maven.org/maven2/org/testng/testng/5.7/testng-5.7.jar&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://central.maven.org/maven2/org/testng/testng/5.7/testng-5.7.jar&lt;/a&gt; returns 404&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14456528" author="agudian" created="Mon, 9 Feb 2015 06:13:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Elad, you may also want to try using surefire 2.18.1 instead of the old 2.13.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14456677" author="tibor17" created="Mon, 9 Feb 2015 14:31:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;@Elad, It is in M2 central, but you should specify classifier=jdk15 in your dependencies for TestNG 5.7&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://central.maven.org/maven2/org/testng/testng/5.7/testng-5.7-jdk15.jar&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://central.maven.org/maven2/org/testng/testng/5.7/testng-5.7-jdk15.jar&lt;/a&gt;  &lt;br/&gt;
Pls check it out and let us know your findings. We would need your test project as a zip file.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14456645" author="tzvatot" created="Wed, 11 Feb 2015 05:03:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;@Tibor, tried it with TestNG 5.7, and it still ignores the excludedGroups defined in the pom.xml file.&lt;br/&gt;
However, if I use -DexcludedGroups=group1 it works as expected.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14456655" author="tibor17" created="Wed, 11 Feb 2015 15:29:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hm, that&apos;s strange. Did you test it with 2.18.1?&lt;br/&gt;
Check it out with 2.18.1, and if the issue still presents, open new ticket related to TestNG.&lt;br/&gt;
We will need your test project in zip attached in JIRA.&lt;br/&gt;
Thx for finding the issue.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14456705" author="tzvatot" created="Thu, 12 Feb 2015 07:32:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes, tried it with 2.18.1. It still happens.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14456710" author="tibor17" created="Fri, 13 Feb 2015 02:09:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;@Elad, Feel free to create new issue in JIRA and attach your test project.&lt;br/&gt;
Thx for finding the issue.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14456716" author="tzvatot" created="Sun, 15 Feb 2015 03:54:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks @Tibor.&lt;br/&gt;
I created a test project that presents this issue.&lt;br/&gt;
But I&apos;m not sure it&apos;s the surefire plugin fault. Rather the failsafe plugin.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here&apos;s the details:&lt;br/&gt;
I created a source class, and a test class. Test class contains a single test method that should fail (assertion does not match).&lt;br/&gt;
The test is annotated with &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;@Test(groups = &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;group1&quot;&lt;/span&gt;)&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;. That group is excluded in the surefire configuration, as well is in the failsafe configuration.&lt;br/&gt;
Now, I&apos;m running:&lt;br/&gt;
1)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;mvn clean install&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;result is that the test is running on &quot;verify&quot; goal. Expected it NOT to run, as it is excluded on all plugins.&lt;br/&gt;
2)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;mvn clean install -DexcludedGroups=group1&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;result is that the test is not running at all, and build succeed. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Since the test is running in the verify goal, I think the blame here is the failsafe plugin.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Anyway, I created a jira for it: &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.codehaus.org/browse/SUREFIRE-1143&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://jira.codehaus.org/browse/SUREFIRE-1143&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17994252" author="olamy" created="Fri, 4 Jul 2025 07:18:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This project has moved from Jira to GitHub Issues. This issue was migrated to &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/maven-surefire/issues/1694&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;apache/maven-surefire#1694&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
